<div id="c17">
<p>David Mathers:</p>

<p>I think you&#8217;re on the right track, but not quite there.  In my view, a product can never be “merely functional.”  If it doesn&#8217;t provoke an emotional response, that&#8217;s critical missing functionality.</p>

<p>Well-designed products minimize mental overhead through elegant simplicity.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by Jacob Rus
 on September  1, 2007 <a href="perfectionism#c17" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
