<div id="c18">
<p>Perfection isn&#8217;t as important as is a well-adapted system.  Determining which functionality best satisfies a majority of the uses for the largest sub-set(s) of your user base will prove more valuable than providing an exceedingly polished set of functions that don&#8217;t map as well to solving the problems your users are trying to solve.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by John Siegrist
 on September  3, 2007 <a href="perfectionism#c18" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
